            <div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:8;--c-lg:7">
              <div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-636_">
                <h5 data-pf-type="Heading2" data-animation="fadeIn" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-637_ pf-heading-1-h3">WHY 12 MONTHS?</h5>
                <h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" data-animation="fadeIn" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-639_ pf-heading-1-h3">For real life support</h3>
                <p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-641_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4">
                  <input type="checkbox" id="compact-23fbdeaf-b4a9-41ba-b20d-306563851b03"/>
                  <span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>You will get far more out of this experience by having time to absorb what you are learning,</strong> miss a call when life gets full, return without feeling behind, and keep moving without pressure. It matters to know that life can happen and the work is still here waiting for you.</span>
              </p>
              <p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-644_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4">
                <input type="checkbox" id="compact-06952e5e-04e4-4f02-b036-7935c7b3a375"/>
                <span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>12 months together means life has room to happen.</strong> A busy season, family needs, travel, illness, unexpected interruptions, beautiful moments, difficult weeks — all of it belongs inside a year. This experience is designed with real life in mind, which means we are not rushing what needs time if we want the kind of change that actually lasts.</span>
              </p>
              <h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" data-animation="fadeIn" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-647_ pf-heading-1-h3">Long-term support creates deeper results</h3>
              <p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-649_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4">
                <input type="checkbox" id="compact-bf51b565-97e9-48be-913b-bd45b3ced00d"/>
                <span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>When someone begins to truly know how you think,</strong> where you tend to get stuck, what matters to you, and what patterns keep repeating, the guidance becomes far more meaningful. There is a different kind of growth that happens when support is steady instead of constantly starting over.</span>
              </p>
              <h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" data-animation="fadeIn" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-655_ pf-heading-1-h3">This is not a quick fix</h3>
              <p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-657_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4">
                <input type="checkbox" id="compact-f18ce154-8a62-4509-8dce-873343940a23"/>
                <span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>We are not simply talking about one area of life or collecting ideas that sound helpful.</strong> This is a lived process where what you are learning meets your relationships, your rhythms, your emotions, your decisions, and the ordinary places life is actually happening.</span>
            </p>
            <p class="sc-hgRQsa gNGIPQ pf-660_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4">
              <input type="checkbox" id="compact-cd448094-105b-4f45-bd86-2c70e8108c7e"/>
              <span class="pf-paragraph-content "><strong>A beautiful life is built over time.</strong> What you want to become does not happen all at once. It happens through repeated attention, honest reflection, and learning how to live differently long enough that what once felt difficult begins to feel natural.</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
